  "guide.title": "## StoryForge User Guide",
  "guide.how_pipeline": "### How does the pipeline work?",
  "guide.pipeline_diagram": "```\nIdea → [Layer 1: Story Creation] → [Layer 2: Drama Simulation] → [Layer 3: Video Script] → Output\n```",
  "guide.layer1_title": "#### Layer 1: Story Creation (create-story)",
  "guide.layer1_desc": "- Create characters with personality, backstory, motivation\n- Build world setting\n- Create detailed outline\n- Write chapters automatically",
  "guide.layer2_title": "#### Layer 2: Drama Simulation (MiroFish-inspired)",
  "guide.layer2_desc": "- **Analysis:** Extract relationships and conflicts between characters\n- **Simulation:** Each character becomes an autonomous AI agent\n- Agents interact freely: post thoughts, react, confront, betray\n- Evaluation system extracts dramatic situations\n- **Enhancement:** Rewrite story with dramatic elements from simulation",
  "guide.layer3_title": "#### Layer 3: Video Script (waoowaoo-inspired)",
  "guide.layer3_desc": "- Create storyboard: shots, camera, mood for each scene\n- Generate image prompts for AI image generation\n- Create voiceover script with emotions\n- Describe character visuals and settings",
  "guide.usage_title": "### How to use",
  "guide.usage_steps": "1. Go to **Settings** → enter API Key and select model\n2. Go to **Full Pipeline** → enter story idea\n3. Adjust parameters as needed\n4. Click **Run Pipeline** and wait\n5. View results in tabs: Story, Simulation, Video, Review\n6. Click **Export files** to save results",
  "guide.api_title": "### Compatible APIs",
  "guide.api_desc": "Supports any OpenAI-compatible API: OpenAI, Anthropic (via proxy), Google Gemini, DeepSeek, Groq, Together AI, OpenRouter, Ollama, etc."
}
